verbs.description: untheologize (third-person singular simple present untheologizes, present participle untheologizing, simple past and past participle untheologized)

entries.meaning: (transitive, rare) To remove the theology from.
examples: […]  as the Chief Justice gives out that he is only waiting the Bishop's arrival to bring forward some strong measures touching the College, and tending to untheologize it.
